<HEADLINE>
<P>
BIG RATE HIKE FOR ASSIGNED-RISK CAR INSURANCE 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
In response to "Assigned-Risk Rates to Rise Average of 85%," Sept. 20: 
</P>
<P>
Now that my auto insurance is being raised from $575 to $1,000 per year (I have 
assigned-risk insurance because my car is old, 1965 model), I suppose I should 
jump for joy for getting a discount from the insurance companies when they get 
both feet in the door with good old no-fault. No way. 
</P>
<P>
I'm going to give myself a 100% discount; no more insurance until the state 
gives me affordable insurance. I would like to see the state add an insurance 
fee ($200) to the license fee on every vehicle. 
</P>
<P>
This probably will never happen because it would be asking our politicians to 
put their hands back in their own pockets. 
</P>
<P>
JEROME HOLBROOK 
</P>
<P>
Inglewood 
</P>
</TEXT>
