<HEADLINE>
<P>
BIG RATE HIKE FOR ASSIGNED-RISK CAR INSURANCE 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Henderson's column is an outstanding example of illogical reasoning, flawed 
comparisons and distortions. 
</P>
<P>
Consider just one: "While the state requires everyone to carry insurance 
(liability only), it has to make sure everyone can afford coverage." Why? 
Driving a vehicle is a privilege, not a constitutional right. 
</P>
<P>
If one elects to steer a 3,000-pound vehicle, a lethal weapon, that person has 
the moral as well as legal obligation to monetarily care for victims of a 
driver's error. And the government should not subsidize such insurance or allow 
driving without coverage. 
</P>
<P>
WALLACE HUNT 
</P>
<P>
Downey 
</P>
