<P>
Women in Film Festival: The four-day Women in Film Festival will open with the 
premiere of director Diane Kurys' family drama "C'est La Vie," Oct. 25, 
organizers of the sixth annual event announced. In all, 47 films and 
documentaries -- written, directed or produced by women -- will screen at the 
festival, which is open to the public at the Directors Guild of America 
headquarters in Hollywood. Among the films screening will be "The Asthenic 
Syndrome," directed by Kira Muratova, from the Soviet Union; "The Big Steal," 
