<HEADLINE>
<P>
SAN DIEGO COUNTY DIGEST: ALPINE 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
A 30-year-old man was in serious condition Tuesday at Sharp Memorial Hospital 
after being shot by a sheriff's deputy Monday night on the Viejas Indian 
Reservation, deputies said. 
</P>
<P>
Keith Grijalva was shot once in his abdomen by Deputy Michael Tverberg during a 
family disturbance call on Viejas Grade Road, a Sheriff's Department spokesman 
said. 
</P>
<P>
The incident occurred at Grijalva's residence on the reservation, about three 
miles east of Alpine. 
</P>
<P>
Tverberg and two other deputies responding to the call at 6:30 p.m. Monday were 
told that an intoxicated man with weapons was threatening to shoot a woman in 
the home, the spokesman said. Tverberg established voice contact with Grijalva, 
who was verbally abusive and told Tverberg he had already killed Beverly Jane 
Cantwell, the spokesman said. 
</P>
<P>
Tverberg forcibly entered the home and Grijalva reacted in a way that made the 
officer fear for his safety and he fired one shot, the spokesman said. Grijalva 
was taken to Sharp Memorial Hospital. 
</P>
<P>
Cantwell apparently had fled to a nearby residence prior to the deputies 
arrival, the spokesman said. 
</P>
<P>
Other details of the shooting were not available and an investigation is 
continuing, the spokesman said. 
</P>
</TEXT>
