<P>
Pacific Bell Proposes Rate Cut: The proposed $73.3-million rate reduction would 
lower the average residential customer's bill by 28 cents a month beginning in 
January. The reduction, part of the California Public Utilities Commission's 
"incentive regulation" plan adopted a year ago, if approved would appear on 
customers' bills as an increase in the credit that they have been receiving for 
the past three years. 
