<TEXT>
<P>
A pro-Iraqi group in the former French colony of Djibouti claimed 
responsibility for a grenade attack last week against a cafe popular with 
French troops in which a boy died and 17 people were injured, officials said. A 
leaflet from the previously unknown group, the Movement for Djibouti Youth, was 
found in a taxi used in the attack on the crowded Cafe de Paris in the bustling 
port. Foreign Minister Roland Dumas had warned that France would retaliate if 
Iraq was linked to the incident. 
