<P>
DISABLED END PROTEST AT MOREHOUSE COLLEGE 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By Associated Press 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<DATELINE>
<P>
ATLANTA 
</P>
</DATELINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Disabled activists ended their occupation of an administration building at 
Morehouse College on Tuesday, leaving the building with a statement from the 
college saying it sympathized with the group's concerns. 
</P>
<P>
The protest by members of ADAPT, or Americans Disabled for Attendant Programs 
Today, had shut down some vital offices in the administration building, but 
classes continued as scheduled. 
</P>
</TEXT>
