<HEADLINE>
<P>
OFFICIALS SEEK CAUSE OF CONVENTION ILLNESSES 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By United Press International 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<DATELINE>
<P>
CHICAGO 
</P>
</DATELINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
City Health Department officials were attempting Tuesday to determine the cause 
of the apparent food poisoning of more than 150 people attending a convention. 
</P>
<P>
The officials said the apparent cause was food served Sunday at a hotel, but 
they added that it could be several days or even weeks before a determination 
is made. A survey of area hospitals showed that at least 155 people were 
treated for symptoms of food poisoning. 
</P>
<P>
The meal at the Hyatt Regency Hotel included a green salad, chicken stuffed 
with wild rice and bread pudding with cream sauce. 
</P>
