<HEADLINE>
<P>
METRO DIGEST / LOCAL NEWS IN BRIEF: SUSPECT ARRESTED AFTER JEWELRY CACHE 
DISCOVERED 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Patrol officers checking on an unrelated dispute at a North Hollywood house 
arrested a suspected thief after discovering suitcases stuffed with an 
estimated 4,000 to 5,000 pieces of allegedly stolen jewelry, police said 
Tuesday. 
</P>
<P>
Burglary detectives and patrol officers spent more than 20 hours cataloguing 
the jewelry after the arrest Monday night of Edmund Sykes, 39, on suspicion of 
robbery and receiving stolen property. 
</P>
<P>
Police said the jewelry -- mostly watches, necklaces, earrings and pins -- is 
believed to have come from dozens of burglaries in Los Angeles. 
</P>
<P>
Detectives have connected some of the jewelry to two residential burglaries in 
the San Fernando Valley and identified Sykes as a suspect in two robberies, Lt. 
Ron LaRue said. 
</P>
</TEXT>
