<HEADLINE>
<P>
METRO DIGEST / LOCAL NEWS IN BRIEF: SUPERVISORS VOTE TO STUDY PARKING LOT OVER 
FREEWAY 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
County supervisors on Tuesday voted to study construction of a double-deck 
parking structure over the Hollywood Freeway in downtown Los Angeles, just west 
of the proposed "West Coast Gateway." 
</P>
<P>
In approving the $350,000 study, supervisors said that construction of the 
parking lot over the freeway between Grand Avenue and Hill Street would free up 
a county parking lot for development of a high-rise office. 
</P>
<P>
County officials are looking to lease county parking lots to private developers 
to raise money to support county operations. Preliminary estimates put the cost 
of the parking structure at $36 million. 
</P>
<P>
The project requires approval of the state Department of Transportation. 
</P>
</TEXT>
