<HEADLINE>
<P>
COLLEGE FOOTBALL REPORT WEEKDAY UPDATE; 
</P>
<P>
USC; 
</P>
<P>
PRICE: WE MADE MARINOVICH'S YEAR 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By JERRY CROWE 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
In his fourth game as USC's quarterback last season, redshirt freshman Todd 
Marinovich led a 91-yard, 18-play touchdown drive in the last 3 1/2 minutes, 
lifting the Trojans to an improbable 18-17 victory over Washington State at 
Pullman, Wash. 
</P>
<P>
In his fourth game as UCLA's quarterback, redshirt freshman Tommy Maddox passed 
for 273 yards and the go-ahead touchdown with 7:55 left, helping the Bruins 
overcome a 10-point second-half deficit in a 30-20 victory over Washington 
State last Saturday at Pullman, Wash. 
</P>
<P>
"They're different in their style," said Cougar Coach Mike Price, who will get 
a second look at Marinovich Saturday night at the Coliseum. "Marinovich is a 
little more deliberate in his throwing motion -- a lot of left-handers are. I 
don't know if they are, but they look like they are. 
</P>
<P>
"Maddox doesn't have that over-the-head delivery. He's got a three-quarters 
sidearm delivery and lets the ball go quickly. But they're both excellent. I 
was very, very impressed with Maddox. And of course, Marinovich -- we made his 
year last year." JERRY CROWE 
</P>
</TEXT>
<SUBJECT>
<P>
FOOTBALL PLAYERS; UNIVERSITY OF SOUTHERN CALIFORNIA; UNIVERSITY OF CALIFORNIA 
AT LOS ANGELES; MARINOVICH, TODD; MADDOX, TOMMY 
</P>
