<P>
BURNS 2ND, CSUN 5TH IN GOLF INVITATIONAL 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Led by Bob Burns' 54-hole total of 218, the Cal State Northridge men's golf 
team finished fifth Tuesday in the 20-team Wolfpack golf invitational at Lake 
Tahoe. 
</P>
<P>
Burns, the defending NCAA Division II individual champion, fired rounds of 78, 
69 and 71 in the two-day meet at the par-72 Edgewood Golf Course to tie for 
second individually. Players shot 27 holes a day. 
</P>
<P>
Northridge finished at 986, 14 strokes behind first-place Nevada Reno, the host 
school. Fred Widicus of Virginia won medalist honors at 214. 
</P>
<P>
Charlie Wi, a freshman from Westlake High, tied for fourth at 219 for Nevada 
Reno. 
</P>
<P>
