<HEADLINE>
<P>
CSUN VOLLEYBALL TEAM OVERTAKES FRESNO STATE 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Behind the 18-kill effort of outside hitter Nancy Nicholls, the Cal State 
Northridge women's volleyball team Tuesday won its third consecutive match, 
dumping Fresno State, 11-15, 17-15, 15-13, 15-7. 
</P>
<P>
Nicholls, a sophomore from Cleveland High, made only six errors in 41 attacks 
as CSUN ran its record to 12-5. 
</P>
<P>
Twins Kathleen and Marianne Dixon combined for 25 kills and Marianne led the 
team in kill percentage at 43.5%. 
</P>
<P>
Setter Beth Welch had 56 assists and seven kills. 
</P>
<P>
The match marked the return of right-side hitter Shelly Swalec, who missed two 
matches with groin and hamstring strains. 
</P>
<P>
The Matadors return to action this weekend at the Nevada Reno Invitational. 
CSUN plays Texas El Paso on Friday at 4:30 p.m. in the tournament opener. 
</P>
</TEXT>
