<P>
PACEWITZ CONVICTED OF MURDER IN STABBING OF ANAHEIM GIRL 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
From Times Staff and Wire Service Reports 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<DATELINE>
<P>
SANTA ANA 
</P>
</DATELINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Michael Robert Pacewitz, who said he killed a 3-year-old girl because he 
thought she was Satan, was found guilty of first-degree murder this morning. 
</P>
<P>
Pacewitz, 21, was also found guilty of the attempted murder of his mother and 
assault with a deadly weapon on her boyfriend in a separate incident at their 
Anaheim apartment in March. That stabbing attack occurred just hours before the 
little girl was stabbed to death at her Fullerton home. 
</P>
<P>
The jury deliberated less than a day before reaching its verdict. 
</P>
<P>
The jurors return tomorrow to determine whether Pacewitz, a former mental 
patient, was sane at the time of the killing. If he is found insane, he would 
be committed to a state hospital for an indeterminate period. 
</P>
<P>
Pacewitz called police in the early morning hours of March 3 and said he had 
just killed 3-year-old Marcelline Onick at the Fullerton apartment where she 
lived with her mother and baby brother. Police found the boy crying not far 
from the girl's mutilated body in a bedroom. She had been stabbed 44 times and 
her head nearly severed with a butcher knife. 
</P>
<P>
The mother had left the children in the care of the baby boy's father, but he 
turned those duties over to a friend whom Pacewitz had gone to see after he 
stabbed his mother. Pacewitz, a friend of the children's mother, Joanne 
Boydston, ended up the lone baby-sitter for them. 
</P>
<P>
Deputy Dist. Atty. Bryan F. Brown contends that Pacewitz killed the little girl 
to get back at his own mother, who considered the girl like a granddaughter. 
Pacewitz was upset with his mother, Elena Fontaine, because he claimed she had 
failed to assist him when he told her he needed emotional help. 
</P>
<P>
Pacewitz claimed to his doctors after his arrest that he thought his mother was 
Satan and was trying to kill him and that he thought Satan had taken over the 
little girl's body. But prosecutor Brown claims Pacewitz concocted the Satan 
story. 
</P>
</TEXT>
