</P>
<P>
SUSPECT CRASHES IN N. HOLLYWOOD 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
From Times Staff and Wire Service Reports 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
A robbery suspect was arrested this morning after a car chase ended with his 
crashing into a fire hydrant and a light pole in North Hollywood, Los Angeles 
police said. 
</P>
<P>
Detective Raymond Rueda said the suspect, Yoon Hong, 18, of Rialto, suffered 
only minor injuries in the 1:15 a.m. crash at Vineland Avenue and Bluffside 
Drive. 
</P>
<P>
He was arrested on suspicion of robbery and was being held in lieu of $20,000 
bail. There were no other injuries. 
</P>
<P>
Police said the incident began about 1 a.m. near Silver Lake and Sunset 
boulevards in Silver Lake when officers on routine patrol came upon a street 
robbery in progress. 
</P>
<P>
The officers saw three young men robbing a fourth man, and the suspects 
scattered and ran in different directions when they saw the police car, Rueda 
said. 
</P>
<P>
One of the suspects ran to a car and sped north on the Hollywood Freeway with 
the patrol car in pursuit. The vehicle left the freeway at Vineland Avenue, and 
the driver turned the vehicle's headlights off, police reported. 
</P>
<P>
At Bluffside Drive, the car went out of control and struck the fire hydrant and 
light pole and came to a stop. 
</P>
<P>
Hong was treated at the scene by paramedics and was being held at the Northeast 
Station. Police were still looking for the two other suspects. The name of the 
robbery victim was not released. 
</P>
</TEXT>
