SINGAPORE AIR ORDERS BOEINGS 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
From Times Wire Services 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<DATELINE>
<P>
SINGAPORE 
</P>
</DATELINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Singapore Airlines today said it has signed a contract with Boeing for 30 
B747-400 aircraft in a deal valued at $5.5 billion. 
</P>
<P>
It said in a statement that the contract covers a firm order placed in January 
this year for 15 planes, including a cargo jet, and options for 15 others. 
Deliveries are scheduled between 1994 and 1998. 
</P>
<P>
Singapore Airlines has on order 20 McDonnell Douglas MD-11 planes worth $3.1 
billion. 
</P>
<P>
The statement said the cargo jet ordered will allow the airline to expand its 
cargo service, which last year accounted for 19% of the airline's total revenue 
of $2.8 billion. 
