Freeway in Orange County. . . . Noting that Riverside County residents pay a 
local half-cent sales tax for freeway improvements, Riverside's transportation 
chief pledged in a letter last week to Caltrans to "exhaust all administrative 
and legal avenues" to kill the toll plan. "The question is the equity of paying 
a toll when most of those using Highway 91 are from San Bernardino and 
Riverside counties, and they have already agreed to pay tax money," Kay 
Ceniceros says. "It is double taxation and ought not to be done." Dallas 
