John H. Taylor, the library's executive director, knew instantly that the 
communique was a hoax. The library does not have Nixon's pardon. After 
examining the fax, which had Gerald R. Ford's middle initial wrong, Taylor 
said: "It is a patent piece of fakery." Dallas Jackson and David Reyes 
