<HEADLINE>
<P>
COLLEGE ROUNDUP; 
</P>
<P>
UCLA NEEDS OVERTIME TO BEAT UC IRVINE IN WATER POLO, 15-12 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Led by Stefan Pollmann's nine goals, the UCLA water polo team defeated UC 
Irvine, 15-12, in overtime in a nonconference game Tuesday at UCLA. 
</P>
<P>
Irvine's Mark Herman scored two goals late in regulation play -- including one 
with 15 seconds remaining -- to tie the score, 12-12, but the Anteaters were 
shut out in the two three-minute overtime periods. 
</P>
<P>
UCLA's Mike Wilmink scored 15 seconds into the first overtime and Javier 
Escobar and Pollmann each scored in the second overtime for the Bruins (15-0), 
the nation's second-ranked team. 
</P>
<P>
Herman led the seventh-ranked Anteaters (7-6) with four goals. Pablo Yrizar 
added three and Steve Froning two. 
</P>
<P>
</P>
<P>
In Golden State Athletic Conference women's volleyball: 
</P>
<P>
Southern California College 3, Christ College Irvine 2 -- Krista Hoover and 
Heather Frewin each had 15 kills for host Southern California (14-13, 1-4 in 
conference) in a 15-10, 14-16, 15-12, 14-16, 15-7 victory. Christ College is 
9-14, 0-5. 
</P>
</TEXT>
