<HEADLINE>
<P>
BRIEFCASE: INTERNATIONAL TRADE 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
Compiled by Cristina Lee / Times staff writer 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Moscow Joint Venture: Americom International Corp. of Irvine and Radisson 
Hotels International of Minneapolis have formed a joint venture with Intourist, 
the Soviet government travel agency, to manage an $80-million hotel and 
business complex Intourist has built in Moscow. 
</P>
<P>
Under the joint venture, called RadAmer-Intourist, Radisson will manage a 
430-room hotel and Americom will oversee a 170-suite business complex. The 
venture will be 50% owned by Intourist, which is building the complex, and 50% 
by RadAmer. Americom owns 80% of RadAmer and Radisson owns 20%. 
</P>
<P>
The agreement is expected to be signed in Moscow within the next two months, 
said Bernard Rome, Americom chairman. Rome said the complex is expected to open 
next spring. 
</P>
</TEXT>
<TYPE>
<P>
