<HEADLINE>
<P>
NIBBLES AND BITS 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
Compiled by Kenneth Williams 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Patricia Trenton, guest curator of the Laguna Art Museum exhibit "California 
Light: 1900-1930," will lecture at the museum on Oct. 11 at 9 a.m. Trenton, who 
holds a doctorate in art history from UC Berkeley, will discuss the ways the 
nine artists in the show (which opens Oct. 12) were inspired by the quality of 
light and color in the California landscape. 
</P>
<P>
Admission: $4.50 general, $3.50 for students and seniors; a continental 
breakfast is included. The museum is at 307 Cliff Drive in Laguna Beach. 
Information: (714) 494-8971. 
</P>
</TEXT>
